# Add Markdown Support to Vite Project

The goal is to enable the import and usage of [.md](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/%E7%87%9F%E9%81%8B%E5%BE%8C%E5%8F%B0/README.md) files within the Voice project. This will allow "setting" or documentation files to be rendered directly in the application.

## User Review Required

> [!NOTE]
> I will configure the project to support importing [.md](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/%E7%87%9F%E9%81%8B%E5%BE%8C%E5%8F%B0/README.md) files as Vue components. This requires installing `unplugin-vue-markdown`.
> If you only need the **text content** of the markdown files (not rendered as HTML/Components), you can already do this without new plugins using `import text from './file.md?raw'`.
>
> Please let me know if you prefer the simple text import (no install needed) or the full component support. I will assume **Component Support** for this plan as it is more powerful.

## Proposed Changes

### Build Configuration

#### [MODIFY] [package.json](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/營運後台/package.json)
- Add `unplugin-vue-markdown` to `devDependencies`.

#### [MODIFY] [vite.config.ts](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/營運後台/vite.config.ts)
- Configure `Markdown()` plugin.
- Add `include: [/\.vue$/, /\.md$/]` to the Vue plugin options to allow [.md](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/%E7%87%9F%E9%81%8B%E5%BE%8C%E5%8F%B0/README.md) extensions to be handled as Vue components.

#### [MODIFY] [tsconfig.json](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/營運後台/tsconfig.json) or [src/vite-env.d.ts](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/營運後台/src/vite-env.d.ts)
- Add type declaration for `*.md` files so TypeScript doesn't complain.

